This paper is about natural language inference (NLI) and neural network models, which are commonly studied in the sub-field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the performance of these models on different datasets, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
